type keyword is used to define custom types.
type TypeName = TypeDefinition;

type Age = number;
let myAge: Age = 25; // âœ… Works
let anotherAge: Age = "25"; // âŒ Error: Type 'string' is not assignable to type 'number'


ğŸ”¹ Using type for Objects
type User = {
    name: string;
    age: number;
  };
  
  const person: User = { name: "Alice", age: 30 }; // âœ… Works
  const anotherPerson: User = { name: "Bob" }; // âŒ Error: Property 'age' is missing
  

  1ï¸âƒ£ Union Types
A Union Type allows a variable to have multiple types
type Status = "success" | "error" | "loading";

let apiStatus: Status = "success"; // âœ… Works
apiStatus = "failed"; // âŒ Error: Type '"failed"' is not assignable to type 'Status'
This is useful for defining strict values a variable can hold.


